cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO 

This paper is about visual tracking, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves learning a graph representation for tracking, which suggests that it may fall under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper uses image features and structured support vector machines, which are commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) and robotics (cs.RO) research.
